(1, 'voldurs Amulet of fire', 'amulet.jpg', 'amulet', 500, 'rare', 26, '+4 strength', 'Voldur\'s Amulet of Fire is a mystical and enchanting artifact steeped in the volatile energies of the elemental plane of fire. Crafted by the renowned wizard Voldur Flameheart, this amulet is a masterpiece of arcane craftsmanship and imbued with the essence of the very flames it seeks to control. The amulet\'s intricate design features a finely wrought golden chain that holds a brilliant crimson gem at its center, reminiscent of a flickering flame frozen in time.\n\nThe gem, said to be a shard of the eternal flame, pulsates with an inner fire that casts a warm and vibrant glow in its vicinity. When worn, the amulet grants its bearer a deep connection to the primal forces of fire, enhancing their magical abilities and conferring protection against flame-related perils. Flames dance ethereally around the amulet, responding to the wearer\'s emotions and intentions.\n\nThe amulet\'s magical properties extend beyond mere aesthetics. It grants the wearer the ability to manipulate fire with an innate mastery, allowing them to conjure flames, control existing fires, and resist the effects of intense heat. Voldur\'s Amulet of Fire is also known to amplify fire-based spells, turning them into more formidable expressions of destructive power. Wizards and sorcerers who seek to specialize in pyromancy find this amulet to be an invaluable tool in their pursuit of mastery over the elemental forces.\n\nHowever, with great power comes great responsibility. The amulet\'s fiery nature is not without its risks, and unwary wielders may find themselves consumed by the very flames they command. Legend has it that Voldur Flameheart, the amulet\'s creator, met a fiery demise when he lost control of the elemental forces he sought to harness. As such, those who possess Voldur\'s Amulet of Fire must tread carefully, for the line between mastery and destruction is as thin as the edge of a well-forged blade.'),
